tip.text: Don't come here alone. The portions are family style, which the waiter conveniently didn't tell me. Wasted food and money. And no "sides" - only meat and bread and salads. Fail by my taxi driver :(
I can't say it's better than Tikal, but if you want a less touristy, more peaceful and nearly equally awe-inspiring experience, don't miss Yaxha. It's Tikal's laid back, greener cousin.
